---

# Project Setup

Clone the repository:

```bash id="clone_repo"
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/ai-sales-visit-logger.git
cd ai-sales-visit-logger
```

Install dependencies:

```bash id="install_deps"
npm install
```

Start the development server:

```bash id="start_project"
npx expo start
```

You can run the app using:

* Expo Go (mobile)
* Web browser

---

# Environment Variables

Create a `.env` file in the root directory:

```
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key
```

This API key is used for generating AI-powered summaries from meeting notes.

Make sure `.env` is added to `.gitignore` so that the API key is not pushed to GitHub.

---

# Architecture Overview

## Data Flow

User enters visit data → visit logs are stored locally using AsyncStorage → logs appear in the visit list → sync service updates sync status.

## Local Persistence

Visit logs are saved locally using AsyncStorage which allows the application to work offline.

## Sync Approach

Each visit contains a `syncStatus` field:

* draft → newly created visit
* syncing → syncing in progress
* synced → successfully synced
* failed → sync failed

Users can retry syncing failed entries from the visit detail screen.

## AI Integration

The app integrates Gemini AI API to generate structured summaries from raw meeting notes.

The generated summary includes:

* Meeting Summary
* Pain Points
* Action Items
* Recommended Next Step

